In the movie, main character Ralphie's father wins a prize that turns out to be a garish lamp in the shape of a woman's leg in a fishnet stocking.

Ralphie's mother despises the novelty after seeing the way her husband covets it and pretends to 'accidentally' break it, leaving the Old Man heartbroken. 

In reality, the lamp has become the most memorable prop--along with its synonymous 'Fra-Gee-Lay' movie quote--from the holiday favorite film.

